narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend QE to other students interested in examining what it means to be queer and have queer sex.
Be prepared for an intense workload, but these books will change the way you view life, LGBTQ issues, and other elements of community building.

Absolutely take this class!! However, if it's not taught by karen (which it sadly won't be), then I would change my recommendation to "Absolutely shop this class!!" It's an amazing topic and one of the best classes I've taken at yale, but karen nakamura made it as good as it was.
The class is an exploration into many different queer and 'queer' identities and really pushes you to reconsider what the term 'queer' means and what it encompasses.
Without a doubt one of the best classes I have taken at Yale, and some of the better intellectual discussions I have had.
